      "solution": "n=int(input())\na=list(map(int,input().split()))\nif len(a)==1:print(a[0])\nelse:\n    while len(a)>1:\n        a=[a[i]+a[~i] for i in range(len(a)//2)]+([a[len(a)//2]] if len(a)&1 else [])\n        print(*a)\n",
      "statement": "Fold a list by summing mirrored pairs (first + last, second + second-last, …).\nIf the list length is odd, carry the middle element unchanged.\nPrint each fold result on its own line until one number remains.\n\nExample:\nInput:\n```\n5\n1 2 4 7 9\n```\n\n\n\nFolds:\n```\n1+9=10, 2+7=9, carry 4 → 10 9 4\n10+4=14, carry 9 → 14 9\n14+9=23 → 23\n```\nOutput:\n```\n10 9 4\n14 9\n23\n```",
